83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
SENATE AMENDMENTS TO
A-ENGROSSED HOUSE BILL 4145
By COMMITTEE ON RULES
March 4
1 On page 1 of the printed A-engrossed bill, line 2, after “amending” delete the rest of the line
2 and delete lines 3 and 4 and insert “sections 10 and 13, chapter 1, Oregon Laws 2023; and declaring
3 an emergency.”.
4 Delete lines 6 through 14 and delete pages 2 through 28 and insert:
5 “SECTION 1. Section 10, chapter 1, Oregon Laws 2023, as amended by section 6, chapter 594,
6 Oregon Laws 2025, is amended to read:
7 “Sec. 10. ORS 166.503, 166.505 and 166.508 and the amendments to ORS 166.412, 166.435, 166.436
8 and 166.438 by sections 6 to 9, chapter 1, Oregon Laws 2023, apply to firearm transfers conducted
9 on or after [March 15, 2026] January 1, 2028.
10 “SECTION 2. Section 13, chapter 1, Oregon Laws 2023, as amended by section 7, chapter 594,
11 Oregon Laws 2025, is amended to read:
12 “Sec. 13. The provisions of ORS 166.355 apply to the manufacture, importation, possession, use,
13 purchase, sale or transfer of a large-capacity magazine occurring on or after [March 15, 2026] Jan-
14 uary 1, 2028.
15 “SECTION 3. The Legislative Assembly does not intend this 2026 Act to render moot or
16 otherwise affect any proceedings pending before the Oregon Supreme Court concerning the
17 constitutionality of Ballot Measure 114 (2022), and the court has authority to issue a judg-
18 ment on the issue of the constitutionality of Ballot Measure 114 (2022) notwithstanding any
19 amendments to chapter 1, Oregon Laws 2023, by this 2026 Act.
20 “SECTION 4. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
21 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
22 on its passage.”.
